# Plain Text Markdown in Underscore Folders

When generating or editing `.md` files under folders whose names start with `_`:

- Use plain Markdown only (headings, paragraphs, lists, links, code fences).
- Do not use raw HTML blocks or inline HTML tags.
- Keep formatting simple and readable; avoid decorative or layout-heavy markup.
- Avoid badges, embedded widgets, and non-text presentation elements.
- Use ASCII by default unless non-ASCII is explicitly required by content.
- Do not add YAML frontmatter unless the user asks for it.

## Preferred Example

```markdown
# Title

A short paragraph in plain language.

- Key point one
- Key point two
```
